Founded in 2012, ByteDance's mission is to inspire creativity and enrich life. With a suite of more than a dozen products, including TikTok, Helo, and Resso, as well as platforms specific to the China market, including Toutiao, Douyin, and Xigua, ByteDance has made it easier and more fun for people to connect with, consume, and create content.

Our group is in charge of developing industrial, commercialized, enterprise-level solutions and products, to meet business requirements in various scenarios, such as Network Infrastructure Construction, System and Application Management, Large-scale Asset Management, Front-desk Service, Audio/Video Broadcasting Service, Server/Conference Room Intelligent Operation, Enterprise Administration, etc. Taking advantage of cutting-edge big data and AI technologies, we are aiming at building a more automated and intelligent enterprise solution infrastructure.

And, you are responsible for:
1. Develop, improve, and maintain web and mobile solutions of IT products;
2. Implement new UI components with a focus on performance and scalability;
3. Design and drive front-end infrastructure of IT R&D Team.
1. BS in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems, Math, or equivalent degree;
2. Expert level knowledge of network, data structure and security is a plus;
3. Decent familiarity with Git;
4. Expert in HTML/CSS,JavaScript(ES6);
5. Experience with SQL/NoSQL Database;
6. Familiarity with UI/UX design and strong ability to work with product managers to improve products;
7. Experience with MVC web framework like Django/Rails/Express is a big plus;
8. Experience with mobile development in iOS/Android, Kotlin/Swift is a big plus;
9. Bring new ideas and technologies into our platform, innovate and iterate.

ByteDance is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At ByteDance, our mission is to inspire creativity and enrich life. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We believe individuals shouldn't be disadvantaged because of their background or identity, but instead should be considered based on their strengths and experience. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

Core Technology Operations - Application Development - Consultant


At Deloitte Consulting LLP, our Core Technology Operations (CTO) specialists provide end-to-end services to help our client organizations manage their portfolio of IT applications, scale and optimize critical business operations, drive speed to outcome and deliver business transformation. We offer a complete range of industry-leading services, providing flexible, recurring resource capacity for client initiatives, projects, tasks, and enhancements which includes quality engineering, systems support, shared services, product engineering, and infrastructure. Our services provide ongoing maintenance, monitoring, and optimization for IT/engineering applications and products around application development, process optimization and automation to help drive speed to outcome, deliver business transformation, and build resilience in an uncertain future.


As a Consultant at Deloitte Consulting, you will be responsible for supporting large complex IT systems - these applications are often high-volume mission critical systems and would provide you an exposure to a broad range of technologies across all Cloud and on prem systems. You will work with global functional and technical teams on engagements that leverage a high degree of automation, the latest technologies and cut across support and development work. You will need to understand functional requirements and should be able to support specific technologies, develop technical designs, develop, customize, and test completing the lifecycle from design to ongoing support.


Work you'll do/Responsibilities:


Provide ongoing support and maintenance for applications, processes and systems as needed;

Develop solutions following established technical design, application development standards and quality processes;

Assess the impacts on technical design because of the changes in functional requirements;

Perform independent code reviews and execute unit tests on modules developed by self and other junior team members on the project;

Write well-designed, efficient, and testable code;

Perform independent code reviews and execute unit tests on modules development by yourself and other team members;

Interact with other stakeholders not limited to end-user clients, Project Manager/Scrum Master, Business Analysts, offshore development, testing and other cross-functional teams.

The Team


Core Technology Operations practitioners work on the design, delivery and support of a variety of solutions that help our clients meet business objectives. These solutions range from large scale ground-up custom developed applications, to Cloud-based development and integration services as well as customizing industry sector-focused packages. As a member of this team, you would get opportunities to work on all adjacent area technologies such as user interface/user experience development, integration services, business rules engine solutions, or Cloud-based services.


Qualifications


Required


Experience working with globally distributed technology teams;
3+ years' experience in application development including "lights on" support services, development and customization;
A solid understanding of the ITIL framework with experience working on other frameworks such as Spring, Struts, Springboot, Hibernate, WebServices (SOAP/REST), etc.;
Current hands-on development skills in at least one of the following: 1) Java; 2) .Net; 3) Mainframe;
A strong understanding of the fundamentals of software engineering with the ability to successfully articulate technology concepts to both a business and a technology audience;
Experience working in an Agile environment, certification is a plus;
Experience working in a multi-vendor environment and with third parties;
3+ years' experience with programming and software development, including analysis, design, development, implementation, testing, maintenance, quality assurance, troubleshooting, upgrading software systems;
Travel up to 50 percent nationally (While 50 percent national travel is a requirement of the role, due to COVID-19, non-essential travel has been suspended until further notice.)

Preferred

Bachelor's degree, preferably in computer science, information technology, computer engineering, engineering or a related discipline;
Industry recognized technology certifications are a plus - AWS, Agile, SAFe, etc.;
Experience with Bot, AI, and ML technologies;
Ability to quickly learn and deliver on analogous technologies not previously worked on;
Ability to communicate clearly across project teams;
Experience in an application support environment which should include working in Cloud (AWS/GCP/Azure);
Strong written and verbal communication skills.
Limited Immigration sponsorship maybe available

